OL,6,FIn 2022, an independent review of
OL,7,Fchildren's services again found high
OL,8,Fvacancy rates and excess workloads.
OL,10,FThe review chair Josh McAlister, a
OL,11,Fformer teacher now a Labour MP, called
OL,12,Ffor a radical overhaul of a "rigid
OL,13,Fsystem stuck in crisis mode and
OL,14,Fdisconnected from the needs of
OL,15,Ffamilies and children they support".
OL,17,FDespite all the good work that is done
OL,18,Fto protect thousands of children every
OL,19,Fyear, social work is often only
OL,20,Fcovered in the media when there is a
OL,21,Fcatastrophic failure.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
